 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 mt-8">GaN V OEM Development Timeline</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Bringing a GaN V charger to market typically follows this timeline: specification and design (2-3 weeks), PCBA prototyping and validation (3-4 weeks), enclosure tooling (4-6 weeks), certification testing (4-6 weeks), and mass production (3-4 weeks after sample approval). Total timeline from concept to first shipment is approximately 16-23 weeks for custom OEM projects. Working with a manufacturer that has pre-certified GaN V platforms can reduce the certification timeline by 4-6 weeks since testing focuses on design variations rather than entirely new submissions.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">For brands needing faster time-to-market, ODM solutions based on existing GaN V platforms can reduce development to 6-8 weeks with MOQ starting at 500 units. WOWOHCOOL offers both OEM and ODM pathways with dedicated engineering support throughout the development process, from initial specification through production ramp-up and ongoing quality monitoring.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mt-4">Whichever pathway you choose, working with a manufacturer that has existing GaN V design experience significantly reduces technical risk. Each generation of GaN brings unique layout and thermal considerations, and a partner with proven production history helps you avoid common design pitfalls that can delay your product launch by weeks or months.</p>

